#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:1
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use Case - Butterfly monitoring"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:6
msgid "Familiarize yourself with the practice use case scenario."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Butterfly Monitoring*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "https://www.gbif.org/occurrence/5177352092[Coenonympha pamphilus (Linnaeus, 1758)] Observed in Sweden by Tobias Karlsson (licensed under http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/[CC-BY-NC 4.0])"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::Use-Case-Practice-Coenonympha-pamphilus.png"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:21
msgid "This narrative was developed as a basis for practical exercises in the biodiversity data mobilization course and the exercise concept and content was developed by Kate Ingenloff and Laura Anne Russell, based on previous work by Alberto González-Talaván, Danny Vélez, Larissa Smirnova, Laura Anne Russell, Mélianie Raymond and Nicolas Noé."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:23
msgid "It is a fictionalized scenario based on a real dataset and is meant only for instructional purposes. The original dataset is attributed to Pettersson L B (2025). Swedish Butterfly Monitoring Scheme (SeBMS). Version 1.12. Department of Biology, Lund University. Sampling event dataset https://doi.org/10.15468/othndo accessed via GBIF.org on 2026-04-12."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:27
msgid "The Swedish Butterfly Network (SBN) has been providing a framework for observational groups to capture data about the occurrence of butterflies (Lepidoptera) on an annual basis since 2009."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:29
msgid "This network of observers use a standard protocol based on Pollard walks to capture this information on paper sheets that they send to the national SBN office. SBN processes the log files and produces an annual report based on the sightings provided by the observation groups, with updated distribution maps and analysis of population trends for some key species."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:31
msgid "The SBN headquarters is mainly staffed with volunteers. The SBN steering committee is trying to identify a more efficient workflow for the creation of digital data because they would like to start publishing these data online to GBIF. Their ultimate objective is to raise the profile of the network and strengthen collaborations with national groups like the Swedish Environmental Protection Agency, the Swedish Transport Administration, and the Swedish County Administration Boards to influence conservation policies for Lepidoptera in Sweden."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:35
msgid "Two different recording methods are used by SBN. One is the point site counts which cover an area with a 25 m radius for 15 min per visit. The other method is fixed-route Pollard walk transects, typically 0.5-3 km in length. These two methods enable the monitoring scheme to assess yearly changes both in the number of butterflies seen and in species composition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:37
msgid "These sampling efforts happen April 1st to September 30th annually. Sites are visited 3-7 times per season."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:39
msgid "The data are, for each species, the sum total of all individuals observed during the visit. For transect sites it is the sum of all individuals from all segments."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:40
msgid "The logs contain observations of species that were actually present at the surveyed sites, but the surveyor would have looked for all species that are included in the survey design. For visits to sites where no observations were made at all, \"SpeciesIncludedInSurvey\" will have a status set to \"Absent\". Additionally, information about whether a visit is a null visit (i.e. true = no survey species observed) or not (i.e. false = one or more survey species were observed) is included (see \"noObservations\")."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:41
msgid "Site coordinates represent midpoints for point sites and centroid midpoints for transect sites."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:42
msgid "Values under stateProvince represent 24 of the 25 Swedish provinces (swe landskap). The 25th province (Lappland) is represented by the 5 areas called ’lappmarker’ (swe)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:43
msgid "Event time is reported for each sampling event as starttime/endtime, or starttime only."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:51
msgid "The SBN office uses groups of volunteers to digitize the paper logs and produce digital spreadsheets. The spreadsheets are very simple and include three datasheets:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:53
msgid "the first captures the information linked to the sampling efforts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:54
msgid "the second the weather conditions and other noted facts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:55
msgid "the third with the species encountered and the number of individuals observed"
msgstr ""

#. type: Target for macro image
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "data-mobilization::Use-Case-Practice-Simple-Spreadsheet.jpg"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:61
msgid "Download the xref:attachment$UC-Practice-exercise-sheet_EN.docx[exercise sheet,opts=download]. (MS Word, 2.9 MB)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:67
msgid "Imagine you are one of the volunteers digitizing the paper logs received at the SBN headquarters. You have received two paper logs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:72
msgid "Use the exercise sheet to provide your answers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:78
msgid "Taking the role of one of the volunteers with advanced computer skills, imagine you have been assigned the responsibility for data quality issues."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:80
msgid "Your main task is to reduce the amount of data that is currently discarded (around a 15%) before processing due to errors and inconsistencies."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:82
msgid "You have received a dataset as the raw product of the digitization effort."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:93
msgid "For this exercise, you will be responsible for publishing the cleaned data online through the GBIF network."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-practice.adoc:95
msgid "The volunteer in charge of data quality has provided an already cleaned and standardized dataset to be published."
msgstr ""

